TEGASEROD: WHAT'S OLD IS NEW AGAIN.
A., in April 2019 tegaserod was once again approved for use in IBS-C under a more restricted labeling, confining use to women under the age of 65 without heart disease or additional cardiovascular risk factors. This review summarizes the regulatory journey of tegaserod, and details the existing pharmacokinetic, physiologic, clinical, and safety data of tegaserod generated over the last two decades. The discussion also examines the future of tegaserod in the treatment of these constipation disorders, as well as its potential role in other related disorders of brain-gut interaction (DGBI).
