The RSPO-LGR4/5-ZNRF3/RNF43 module in liver homeostasis, regeneration and disease.
The RSPO-LGR4/5-ZNRF3/RNF43 module is fine-tuning WNT/ß-catenin signaling in several tissues and is essential for hepatic WNT/ß-catenin activity. In this review article, we recapitulate the role of the RSPO-LGR4/5-ZNRF3/RNF43 module during liver development, homeostasis, metabolic zonation, regeneration and disease. We further discuss the controversy around LGR5 as a liver stem cell marker.
